<item>
            <title>[SPARK-1395] Cannot launch jobs on Yarn cluster with &quot;local:&quot; scheme in SPARK_JAR</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1395</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you define SPARK_JAR and friends to use &quot;local:&quot; URIs, you cannot submit a job on a Yarn cluster. e.g., I have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SPARK_JAR=local:/tmp/spark-assembly-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT-hadoop2.3.0-cdh5.0.0.jar&lt;br/&gt;
SPARK_YARN_APP_JAR=local:/tmp/spark-examples-assembly-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And running SparkPi using bin/run-example yields this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;14/04/02 13:23:33 INFO yarn.Client: Preparing Local resources&lt;br/&gt;
Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.io.IOException: No FileSystem for scheme: local&lt;br/&gt;
